                    <h4>What is the Philippine Electrical Code (PEC)?</h4>
                    <p>The <strong>Philippine Electrical Code (PEC) 2017</strong> is the primary standard governing all electrical installations in the Philippines. It is published and maintained by the <strong>Institute of Integrated Electrical Engineers of the Philippines (IIEE)</strong> and is enforceable under the Philippine Electrical Engineering Act (R.A. 7920).</p>
                    <div class="info-box blue" style="margin-top:12px;">
