              <!-- Roughing-In Concept -->
              <div class="card">
                <div class="section-header">
                  <div class="section-num">3</div>
                  <div>
                    <span class="session-label">Topic 3</span>
                    <h2>Roughing-In Concept</h2>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div style="padding:20px 24px;">
                  <div class="topic-block">
                    <h4>Definition and Purpose</h4>
                    <p><strong>Roughing-in</strong> is the phase of electrical installation that involves installing conduits, electrical boxes, and raceways <em>before</em> walls, ceilings, and floors are finished (plastered/painted). It creates the pathways and mounting locations for all future wiring and devices.</p>
                    <div class="info-box green" style="margin-top:10px;">
                      <span class="ib-icon">&#10003;</span>
                      <div><strong>Remember:</strong> No wires are pulled during roughing-in (except in some applications). The conduit system must be complete and inspected before the building envelope is closed.</div>
                    </div>
                    <h4 style="margin-top:18px;">Roughing-In Sequence</h4>
                    <p>The correct sequence for roughing-in work is:</p>
                    <ol style="padding-left:20px; margin-top:8px; font-size:14px; color:var(--gray-700); line-height:1.7;">
                      <li><strong>Plan and Layout</strong> — Mark outlet, switch, and junction box locations on walls using chalk or pencil. Consult the electrical floor plan.</li>
                      <li><strong>Conduit Installation</strong> — Run conduits from the main panel/sub-panel to all device locations. Use straps/supports to secure.</li>
                      <li><strong>Box Installation</strong> — Mount utility boxes, switch boxes, and junction boxes at marked locations per PEC mounting heights.</li>
                      <li><strong>Cable Pulling</strong> — Pull wires/cables through the installed conduit system.</li>
                      <li><strong>Inspection</strong> — Rough-in inspection by authorized inspector before walls are closed.</li>
                    </ol>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Conduit Types -->
              <div class="card">
                <div class="section-header">
