                    <h4>Philippine/PEC Wire Color Coding</h4>
                    <p>The PEC specifies color coding for wiring to ensure safe identification of conductors. Consistent application prevents dangerous mix-ups during installation and maintenance.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="wiring-visual">
                    <div style="color:#94a3b8; font-size:11px; margin-bottom:10px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:1px;">Wire Color → Terminal Identification</div>
                    <div class="wire-row">
                      <div class="wire-swatch" style="background:#1a1a1a; border:1px solid #555;"></div>
                      <span class="wire-label">Black (Hot)</span>
                      <span class="wire-terminal">→ BRASS terminal (gold-colored screw)</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="wire-row">
                      <div class="wire-swatch" style="background:#f5f5f5; border:1px solid #888;"></div>
                      <span class="wire-label">White (Neutral)</span>
                      <span class="wire-terminal">→ SILVER terminal (silver-colored screw)</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="wire-row">
                      <div class="wire-swatch" style="background:#22c55e;"></div>
                      <span class="wire-label">Green / Bare (Ground)</span>
                      <span class="wire-terminal">→ GREEN screw terminal (ground lug)</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="wire-row">
                      <div class="wire-swatch" style="background:#ef4444;"></div>
                      <span class="wire-label">Red (Hot — 240V / 3-wire)</span>
                      <span class="wire-terminal">→ Second brass terminal or second hot leg</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="info-box blue" style="margin-top:10px;">
                    <span class="ib-icon">&#128204;</span>
                    <div><strong>Memory Aid — B-B, W-S, G-G:</strong> <em>Black → Brass</em>, <em>White → Silver</em>, <em>Green → Green screw</em>. This applies to all standard 120V outlet and switch wiring.</div>
                  </div>
